00:28:25,420 --> 00:28:30,361
shuddha iccha, to be of that level.

194
00:28:32,637 --> 00:28:35,599
 Now, there is no competition

195
00:28:37,134 --> 00:28:46,679
between A and B. We don't say that, “You
got the first prize for coming out of the

196
00:28:46,704 --> 00:28:55,737
Sahastrara” (laughing) or we don't say,
“You have the second prize.” There's nothing

197
00:28:55,762 --> 00:29:06,630
like first, second in Sahaja Yoga, because
we are not running the race. There’s no

198
00:29:06,655 --> 00:29:14,255
competition between us. Whatever we are doing
is for our own satisfaction. Now think of

199
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:20,184
something. There are five people who are running.
Now they have to think, out of these five

200
00:29:20,184 --> 00:29:30,602
people, who goes first. Here it is the other
way round: The five people are meditating;

201
00:29:30,844 --> 00:29:40,449
now everyone individually has to see for himself
if he satisfies himself or not, nobody else

202
00:29:40,474 --> 00:29:46,323
is going to give you a certificate. It is
you who has to give certificate to yourself,

203
00:29:46,323 --> 00:29:51,254
honestly. It's a very different position.

204
00:29:51,254 --> 00:30:01,935
It is you, your Sahastrara and your attention
and you have to see, within yourself, “How

205
00:30:01,960 --> 00:30:17,083
far have I realised my own powers, my own
compassion, my own personality?” You’ll

206
00:30:17,108 --> 00:30:27,919
have to test it yourself. It is you are the
one who decides. When you are the one who

207
00:30:27,944 --> 00:30:38,098
is running, it is you are the one who decides
without running, then what is the question

208
00:30:38,123 --> 00:30:49,767
of competition? The whole thing disappears
into nothing.

209
00:30:50,980 --> 00:31:00,900
As I told you the other day, an analogy that,
if you are looking at the mirror, then you

210
00:31:01,432 --> 00:31:10,615
are the one who is observing, your reflection
is the one that is observed and there is the

211
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:21,319
action of seeing, so you are in 3 dimensions.
But supposing you become the mirror yourself,

212
00:31:25,478 --> 00:31:34,857
the whole process is reversed: You see yourself.
You don't have to see because you are seeing

213
00:31:34,882 --> 00:31:43,605
it all the time, it's just spontaneous. In
the same manner, when it comes to Sahastrara,

214
00:31:43,844 --> 00:31:51,630
it is your Sahastrara itself gives you the
full idea as to how you are. The diagnosis

215
00:31:51,655 --> 00:31:59,683
comes from your own Sahastrara. Your own Sahastrara
tells you what centres are catching because

216
00:31:59,708 --> 00:32:08,736
all the peethas of these seven centres are
in the Sahastrara. As if the Sahastrara is

217
00:32:08,764 --> 00:32:17,018
now watching yourself and reporting to you,
“See, this is wrong with you. This is wrong

218
00:32:17,043 --> 00:32:23,274
with you, this is wrong with you.” So, Sahastrara
being the best well-wisher that you have,

219
00:32:23,274 --> 00:32:29,944
gives you the right information about yourself,
so the best is that you correct yourself.

220
00:32:29,944 --> 00:32:39,423
So then, achieve that perfect state: that
is what you have to do. But once you have

221
00:32:39,448 --> 00:32:47,115
achieved the perfect state, you have achieved
your aim, you have no aim left. Like the lights

222
00:32:47,140 --> 00:32:53,404
now, till you have to make the lights, you
had to work hard, make the lights, put them

223
00:32:53,404 --> 00:33:01,639
right, do everything that is necessary. But
once it is made and the light comes into it,

224
00:33:01,664 --> 00:33:14,551
then the job of the light is to give the light.
So the first function is over.

225
00:33:18,175 --> 00:33:25,175
Now the second function is to give it back.

226
00:33:25,624 --> 00:33:32,174
You reach your aim, your destination. For
example, I had to come here. Alright? So I

227
00:33:32,174 --> 00:33:40,629
come all the way from My house, come in the
car, walking and come and sit down here. Now

228
00:33:40,654 --> 00:33:48,498
it’s finished that part, over. Now I don'
t have to walk, otherwise I’ll be all the

229
00:33:48,523 --> 00:34:02,032
time running. So, all this mad race of this
brain stops. For what should it be used now?

230
00:34:03,134 --> 00:34:15,669
For enjoying the peace, for enjoying the joy,
for enjoying the collectivity. So, the labour

231
00:34:15,694 --> 00:34:24,399
or the hard work or you can also say the planning
of the future finishes off. Only thing now

232
00:34:24,424 --> 00:34:28,434
you have got it, so better enjoy it.

233
00:34:28,434 --> 00:34:40,639
It’s like you are coming from outside, you
are running, you are very hungry, you want

234
00:34:40,664 --> 00:34:50,069
to reach home. Once you reach home, then the
food is served to you. Now what's your aim?

235
00:34:50,094 --> 00:34:56,214
Nothing, but to enjoy the food for which you
were running. But after that also, if you

236
00:34:56,214 --> 00:35:07,099
start running, then one should say it is absolute
stupidity! But the capacity of enjoyment only

237
00:35:07,124 --> 00:35:18,678
comes when your Sahastrara is absolutely open.
Otherwise the capacity to enjoy is much less

238
00:35:19,594 --> 00:35:27,175
and you become like a person who is running
all the time after something which you never

239
00:35:27,200 --> 00:35:35,369
achieve. There are many like that. All their
lives they’re like mad, you know. They are

240
00:35:35,394 --> 00:35:43,538
working morning till evening, everyday, achieving
nothing! Next day again get up, again running!

241
00:35:43,563 --> 00:35:50,563
All their lives running like this till their
foot is in the grave, they are still running.

242
00:35:52,803 --> 00:36:02,008
But after getting to Sahaja Yoga, you stop
all these activities and leave it to your

243
00:36:02,033 --> 00:36:13,485
Sahaja Yoga to work, to your Sahastrara to
work it out. And it works out. You don't have

244
00:36:13,510 --> 00:36:18,914
to rush. You don't have to be so competent.
You don't have to write down everything. You

245
00:36:18,939 --> 00:36:25,578
don't have to think of planning everything.
Just everything works out and it works out

246
00:36:25,603 --> 00:36:31,654
beautifully. The only thing that one has to
do is to accept whatever is happening for

247
00:36:31,654 --> 00:36:45,207
our good. Even in small, small things. For
today's delay in the puja, is the desire of

248
00:36:45,232 --> 00:36:53,449
some people who wanted to give you some sort
of a … I shouldn't say that, but some secret

249
00:36:53,474 --> 00:36:59,394
show was going to be there and they didn't
want any light. So they were thinking, “What

250
00:36:59,394 --> 00:37:03,354
will happen – the puja will be over by about
